 social history, the development of civil liberties and of policing in Britain, as well as anyone interested in this enduring topic. Included is a foreword by Clive Emsley, Emeritus Professor in History at the Open University, and widely regarded as the doyen of police history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivil rightszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aPublic policy (Law)zGreat Britain. 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / General.2bisacsh  aCriminal Investigation Department.  aHome Office.  aLiberal Internationalism.  aNational Council for Civil Liberties.  aRonald Kidd.  aSpecial Branch.  acivil liberties.  anon-party ideology.  apacifist groups.  aplain clothes police officers.  apolicing.  apolitical expression.  apolitical extremes.  apressure group.  apublic attention.  apublic order.  awomen's organisations.1 aClark, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEmsley, Clive, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526129581423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526129581/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles